title: MQM’s Syed Muhammad Usman wins PS-100 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Muttahida Qaumi Movement (MQM), Syed Muhammad Usman has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-100, Karachi East-IV, by securing 21,970 votes.
According to unofficial result issued by Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Haider Ali Imrani, Pakistan People’s Party Parliamentarians’ (PPPP), who bagged vote 15,241.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 31.24%.
